                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fad" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>fad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нога</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>foot</q></abv:tr></sense><re><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Входит во множество сложных слов: </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">It is a part of many compound words: </note><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fadqūl</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>щиколотка</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>ankle</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fadnīz</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>болезнь ног</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (у скота)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about cattle)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>foot illness</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (у скота)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about cattle)</note></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fadat</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>возможность</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>opportunity</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fadʒu</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ход шагом</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>walking</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fadxos</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подстилка из травы в обуви</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>underlayer made of grass for shoes</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>bæǧæmvad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>босой</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>barefooted</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fælmænvad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мягконогий</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в смысле ‘податливый’)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (meaning ‘compliant’)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>with soft feet</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в смысле ‘податливый’)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (meaning ‘compliant’)</note></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>qæbærvad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>крепконогий</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>with strong feet</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ræwvad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>легконогий</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>with light feet</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cybyrvad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>коротконогий</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>with short feet</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cyppærvadygæj</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>галопом</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>at a gallop</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>dælfædty</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в ногах</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>at the foot</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>wælfad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подъем ноги</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>wrist (of a foot)</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>dælfadbos</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>штрипка</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>strap</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cæfxad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подкова</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>horseshoe</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из %icæg-fad%i) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(из %icæg-fad%i) </note></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>særfad</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>порядок</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („голова-нога“)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (lit. ‘head-foot’)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>order</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („голова-нога“)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (lit. ‘head-foot’)</note></sense></re></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейское слово. Удержалось в большинстве иранских и индоевропейских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>pād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>рā, pāl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/> <w>pāδ, pēδ, pōδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pūδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/> <w>pud</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>pūd, pöδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/> <w>pēδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pāla</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>pōda</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*pāδ%ra%r(рʼδ)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>pāa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %ipāδa%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %ipāδa%i)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>раδ-</w> <gloss><q>нога</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>рāδа-</w> <gloss><q>шаг</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pāda-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πόυσ (πωσ), ποδός</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pes, pedis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/> <w>fotus</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/> <w>foot</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Fuss</w> <gloss><q>нога</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>peda</w> <gloss><q>след</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w>pādas</w> <gloss><q>подошва</q></gloss></mentioned>. В славянских языках этот же корень наличен в словах <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/> <w>пеший</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>под</w> <gloss><q>низ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>падать</w></mentioned>. Вариацию этого же слова представляет ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæd"/> ‘след’. О названиях частей тела см. под <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/> ‘голова’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/> ‘рука’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cong"/> ‘рука’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zæng"/> ‘голень’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zonyg"/> ‘колено’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aǧd"/> ‘ляжка’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sin"/> ‘бедро’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>17, 78, 118</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A general Indo-European word. It retained in majority of Iranian and Indo-European words: <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>pād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>рā, pāl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/> <w>pāδ, pēδ, pōδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pūδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/> <w>pud</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>pūd, pöδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/> <w>pēδ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pāla</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>pōda</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*pāδ%ra%r(рʼδ)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>pāa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %ipāδa%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %ipāδa%i)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>раδ-</w> <gloss><q>foot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>рāδа-</w> <gloss><q>step</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pāda-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πόυσ (πωσ), ποδός</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pes, pedis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/> <w>fotus</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/> <w>foot</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Fuss</w> <gloss><q>foot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>peda</w> <gloss><q>footprint</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w>pādas</w> <gloss><q>sole</q></gloss></mentioned>. In Slavic languages, the same root is present in words <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/> <w>пеший</w> <gloss><q>pedestrian</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>под</w> <gloss><q>bottom</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>падать</w> <gloss><q>fall</q></gloss></mentioned>. A variation of the same word is Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæd"/> ‘footprint’. About names of body parts see under <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/> ‘head’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/> ‘hand’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cong"/> ‘hand’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zæng"/> ‘leg’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zonyg"/> ‘knee’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aǧd"/> ‘haunch’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sin"/> ‘hip’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>17, 78, 118</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><note type="internal">надо вставить пример в посткоммент к последнему сабэнтри</note></entry></body></text></TEI>